-- China commerce ministry says confident of achieving annual trade target
-- By Aileen Wang and Jonathan Standing
-- Thu May 15, 2014 10:48PM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, May 16 (Reuters) - China's commerce ministry said on Friday it was confident the country could achieve its target of 7.5 percent growth in total trade this year.

"We are confident of achieving the annual trade growth target this year after making arduous efforts," ministry spokesman Shen Danyang told reporters at a regular briefing. "Generally speaking, we keep a cautiously optimistic view on the trade performance this year."